[SN]TITLE[SN]
Trial date set for Cardiff hotel murder accused Sammy Almahri

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man charged with the murder of a Cardiff woman, whose body was found in a hotel room, will stand trial in January.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
US national Sammy Almahri, 44, denies murdering Nadine Aburas, 31, who was found at the city's Future Inn on December 31, 2014.
On Wednesday, Judge Eleri Rees set a date of 12 January for the start of his trial.
The hearing took place in Mr Almahri's absence at Cardiff Crown Court.
He was arrested by police agencies in Tanzania, east Africa, at the end of January after an international search.
